result.execSummary:
The defendant Roderick V Tyree was found guilty of the following charge(s) in this case.

  • Misappropriate ID Info - Obtain Money [Modifiers: PTAC, as a Party to a Crime], a class H felony, Wisconsin Statutes 943.201(2)(a).
  • Misappropriate ID Info - Obtain Money [Modifiers: PTAC, as a Party to a Crime], a class H felony, Wisconsin Statutes 943.201(2)(a).

Charge(s) in this case were read in to this or other case(s). A "read in" charge is a charge that is dismissed as part of a plea agreement, however:

  • The defendant agrees to have the court consider the charge(s) when sentencing for another crime, under Wis. Stats. 973.20(1g)(b); and
  • The defendant cannot be prosecuted for these charge(s) in the future.

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

Defendant Roderick V Tyree in court, in custody, with attorney Chad Allen Lanning.   Brian J. Juech appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  Recommendations by the State.  Arguments by the Defense.  Statement by defendant.

Court orders the following: 

Count 1:
- Total sentence: 4 years 6 months (Initial Confinement: 1 year 6 months, Extended Supervision: 3 years).  Credit for 105 days.  Extended Supervision may be transferred to Ohio.
- Defendant IS NOT eligible for Challenge Incarceration
- Defendant IS NOT eligible for Substance Abuse Program
- Cash bail to be refunded to poster.
- Court costs of $278.00 to be paid as a Condition of Extended Supervision.
- Restitution in the amount of $3,697.72 to be paid as a Condition of Extended Supervision as follows:  $1,694.36 to BMO Harris Bank; $2,003.36 to Walmart
- Extradition costs of $2,817.96 to be paid as a Condition of Extended Supervision
- DNA Surcharge of $250.00 to be paid as a Condition of Extended Supervision.
- Defendant to provide DNA sample, if not yet provided, immediately if in custody otherwise within (3) business days at the Waukesha County Sheriff Department.
- Conditions of Extended Supervision:  Obtain GED or high school diploma.  Maintain full-time employment and/or school.  Follow through with any treatment/counseling recommended by Agent.  No contact with codefendant.

Count 2:
- Total sentence: 4 years 6 months (Initial Confinement: 1 year 6 months, Extended Supervision: 3 years) CONSECUTIVE to Count 1.  Extended Supervision may be transferred to Ohio.
- Defendant IS NOT eligible for Challenge Incarceration
- Defendant IS NOT eligible for Substance Abuse Program
- Court costs of $278.00 to be paid as a Condition of Extended Supervision.
- DNA Surcharge waived
- DNA sample waived
- Conditions of Extended Supervision:  Same as Count 1.
